President Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Wyoming due to flooding that occurred from June 7 to June 22, 2017. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the State and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.